content:
When you define an sfdcRegister transformation, you set the action attribute to sfdcRegister and specify the parameters. This table describes the input parameters:

PARAMETER	REQUIRED?	VALUE
alias	Yes	API name of the registered dataset. Must be unique among other dataset aliases in your organization.
name	Yes	Display name of the registered dataset.
source	Yes	Node in the dataflow definition file that identifies the dataset to register.

Optional parameters:
rowLevelSharingSource	The API name of the object from which to inherit sharing, used for row-level security.
rowLevelSecurityFilter	The predicate used to apply row-level security on the dataset when created.

Examples:
"rowLevelSharingSource": "Opportunity"
"rowLevelSecurityFilter": "'OwnerId' == "$User.Id""

To change sharing or security settings after creating a dataset, edit the dataset.
title: Configuring sfdcRegister Transformation Parameters
